article.description: — Maleeck Harden-Hayes had 15 points and nine rebounds as North Dakota State got past Oral Roberts 61-54 on Friday night.
article.headline: North Dakota St. beats Oral Roberts 61-54
article.linkText: North Dakota St. beats Oral Roberts 61-54
article.story: FARGO, N.D. -- — Maleeck Harden-Hayes had 15 points and nine rebounds as North Dakota State got past Oral Roberts 61-54 on Friday night. Sam Griesel had 13 points and eight rebounds for North Dakota State (11-8, 9-2 Summit League), which earned its fifth consecutive home victory. Jarius Cook added 11 points. Rocky Kreuser had three blocks. Tyree Eady, whose 11.0 points per game heading into the matchup was second on the Bison, scored three points. He made 17 percent from behind the arc (1 of 6). Kevin Obanor had 26 points and 11 rebounds for the Golden Eagles (9-8, 6-3). Max Abmas added 20 points. RJ Glasper had six rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
